<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1746731 lazyload lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Chia-pudding.-Photo-Cooking-Classy-399x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1920" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Chia-pudding.-Photo-Cooking-Classy-399x598.jpg 399w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Chia-pudding.-Photo-Cooking-Classy-768x1152.jpg 768w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Chia-pudding.-Photo-Cooking-Classy-1024x1536.jpg 1024w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Chia-pudding.-Photo-Cooking-Classy-160x240.jpg 160w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Chia-pudding.-Photo-Cooking-Classy-320x480.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Chia-pudding.-Photo-Cooking-Classy-400x600.jpg 400w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Chia-pudding.-Photo-Cooking-Classy.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> A pudding is a sweet dessert made of a mixture of ingredients that are cooked or thickened and typically served cold. They can be made with a variety of ingredients such as milk, cream, eggs, sugar, and various flavours like chocolate, vanilla, or fruit. Puddings are often eaten as a dessert or a snack and can be served in bowls, cups, or glasses. Chocolate Pudding – A rich and creamy pudding made with chocolate, milk, sugar, and corn-starch. Vanilla Pudding – A classic pudding made with vanilla extract, sugar, corn-starch, and milk. Rice Pudding – A creamy pudding made with cooked rice, milk, sugar, and spices like cinnamon and nutmeg. Tapioca Pudding – A sweet pudding made with small tapioca pearls, sugar, and milk. Bread Pudding – A dessert made with stale bread, eggs, milk, sugar, and spices like cinnamon and nutmeg. Lemon Pudding – A tangy pudding made with lemon juice, sugar, and corn-starch. Banana Pudding – A creamy pudding made with mashed bananas, vanilla, and milk. Apple Pudding – A sweet pudding made with cooked apples, sugar, and spices like cinnamon and nutmeg. 